dct_title_s: West Indies, Hispaniola--south coast, Dominican Republic, approaches to Barahona and Punta Palenque (Raster Image)
dct_description_sm: Prepared and published by the Defense Mapping Agency. Depths shown by isolines and soundings. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. "From surveys by Dominican Republic and U.S. Navy to 1985." "Copyright 1995 by the United States government. No copyright claimed under title 17 U.S.C." "Soundings in meters." Insets: Barahona. Scale 1:10,000 -- Punta Palenque. Scale 1:25,000. Includes compilation diagram. Map No.25842.
This map is part of a collection of scanned and georeferenced nautical charts produced by the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA).
This layer is presented in the WGS84 coordinate system for web display purposes. Downloadable data are provided in native coordinate system or projection.
